          %h4 Democratizing wine since 2013
        %p Bloocher is a #{link_to "boontling", "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boontling"} word, one of the meanings of which is "bullshitter."  If we're honest as insiders, bullshit is a lot of what our industry is built on.  But somewhere underneath is one truth:  <em>We like some wines are better than others.</em>  

        %p Some of wine quality is about the fruit, some is about winemaker skill, some is about what food its paired with.  But a lot has to do with the winelover, what mood she's in, how much she likes person she's drinking it with, what the weather is like, and how much she likes the view.  By giving wine lovers, winemakers, and vineyardists a place to share raw information, it is our view that some of this bullshit can be stripped away.  

           
             
